    "what_description": "Eurya sericea is a species of flowering plant in the family Pentaphylacaceae. It is an evergreen shrub or small tree that grows up to 5 meters in height, with a grey-brown bark and a sericeous (silky) pubescence on the younger stems and leaves. The leaves are opposite, elliptic to ovate, and 2-5 cm long, with a leathery texture and crenulate margins. The inflorescence is a corymb, bearing small, white to yellowish flowers with 5 petals and a 5-lobed calyx. The plant is native to China, India, and Southeast Asia, where it grows in subtropical forests and mountainous regions.",
